{
  "texts": [
    "on doping away from integer filling.",
    "As underscored by the \"lobe principle\", q IVC is set by a delicate energetic competition between various factors that shape the renormalized symmetric dispersion out of which the IKS state evolves; as such, the robustness of the IKS state can be viewed as a consequence of its ability to respond to various changes by adjusting q IVC while remaining in the same phase.",
    "Furthermore, the evolution of q IVC with doping is nontrivial, and may provide one route to explaining rotation of a nematic superconducting order parameter with doping reported in Ref.",
    "[275] 66.Turning to thermodynamics, we observe that the compressibility computed within Hartree-Fock for strained TBG in the regime where IKS order is prevalent is broadly compatible with the reported \"cascade\" features seen in experiments [237,265].",
    "That said, it is by now reasonably widely believed that the cascades primarily give evidence for the formation of local moments, rather than serve as a sensitive test of the precise nature of the low-temperature state [52]."
  ]
}